Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.39,0:00:18.36,Lucy-Song-Title,,0,0,0,,[I want to be a rainbow]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.64,0:00:29.82,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa hoshifuru yoru ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.07,0:00:36.75,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono tomoshibi wo keshi wa shinai to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.03,0:00:47.88,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.13,0:00:56.81,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru wo yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.09,0:01:08.70,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.98,0:01:20.59,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.87,0:01:26.43,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.71,0:01:36.23,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.64,0:00:29.82,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.07,0:00:36.75,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.03,0:00:47.88,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.13,0:00:56.81,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.09,0:01:08.70,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.98,0:01:20.59,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.87,0:01:26.43,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.71,0:01:36.23,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.61,0:01:53.53,Lucy-Ep-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(325,306.667)\fade(375,400)}Ep. 41 -  Strange People in a Strange City
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.69,0:02:16.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,She's fallen asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.43,0:02:40.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,She's asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.54,0:02:41.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.89,0:02:46.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That girl looks absolutely lovely when she sleeps.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.22,0:02:47.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,She is a lovely girl, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.86,0:02:51.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope she regains her memory in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.36,0:02:52.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'll see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.45,0:02:56.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But what will we do if morning comes and she still doesn't remember anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.59,0:02:58.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Remember what doctor said?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.54,0:03:00.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sooner or later, her memory will return.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.99,0:03:03.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,One way or another, isn't it awfully curious?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.65,0:03:09.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To suddenly forget everything -\Nher own name, her parents and her home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.22,0:03:12.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But she didn't forget how to speak, did she?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.02,0:03:15.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,She only forgot things pertaining herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.60,0:03:17.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I suppose that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.60,0:03:21.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't see the moment\Nof her getting hit by a carriage myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.86,0:03:24.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But the impact must've been really strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.37,0:03:26.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! A runaway horse!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.91,0:03:28.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Runaway horse! A runaway horse!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.83,0:03:30.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Run away! Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.11,0:03:47.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! It's heading for the city!\NStop it, someone! It's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.83,0:03:56.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Madam, did you want to see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.13,0:03:57.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.51,0:04:01.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You see, there's a girl sleeping on the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.79,0:04:02.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.89,0:04:06.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When she fell asleep,\Nshe still hadn't regained her memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.82,0:04:07.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.21,0:04:11.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But we believe she might regain it tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.51,0:04:14.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When morning comes,\Nplease check on her every hour or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.14,0:04:17.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If she remembers her name\Nand her parents' name when she wakes up,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.47,0:04:19.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,please let me know at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.91,0:04:22.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Um. No matter how early it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.42,0:04:23.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.16,0:04:25.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.69,0:04:27.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I'm counting on you, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.66,0:04:28.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.41,0:04:34.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The rain almost stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.20,0:04:36.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. So it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.22,0:04:39.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where could Lucy have gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.54,0:04:43.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You don't suppose she could've already\Nreturned home by now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.72,0:04:45.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That'd sure be good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.69,0:04:48.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When it's {\i1}this{\i0} late,\NI'm sure she had already returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.14,0:04:56.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.65,0:05:00.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you hear some noise\Ncoming from the front just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.78,0:05:02.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't hear anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.44,0:05:04.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate, how is it?\NCan you see anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.97,0:05:06.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.26,0:05:09.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it seems the rain had stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.98,0:05:13.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's really irresponsible of her\Nto be out till so late.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.04,0:05:15.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure dad and John found her already.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.82,0:05:17.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'd like to hope for.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.83,0:05:20.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's so foolish, when it's this late...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.42,0:05:25.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was Little.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.18,0:05:31.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now we know for sure -\NLucy must've returned already.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.53,0:05:40.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You found Lucy, right, Little?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.67,0:05:43.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it's only the two of them returning!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.84,0:05:47.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Lucy? Lucy returned, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.39,0:05:58.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Still not here, is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.34,0:05:59.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.83,0:06:01.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.53,0:06:04.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It seems Lucy is not returning tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.51,0:06:08.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,She must've stayed overnight at some deserted house.\NAfter all, she's ten already.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.80,0:06:12.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure she's well aware of how concerned we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.22,0:06:17.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Supposing... I'm not saying it'll happen,\Nbut supposing she doesn't return tomorrow either...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.69,0:06:19.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then we'll go look for her once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.88,0:06:21.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please let me help you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.54,0:06:23.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right, but I know you have job...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.77,0:06:25.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take a day off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.61,0:06:27.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, I can't allow that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.19,0:06:29.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine. She'll come home tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.11,0:06:32.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, that's what I think as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.08,0:06:35.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, Mr. Popple, I would leave you for tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.90,0:06:37.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I really appreciate it, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.61,0:06:39.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.67,0:06:42.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. I'll walk you home for a short while.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.44,0:06:45.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Well, goodnight then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.68,0:06:52.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.34,0:06:54.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You had to walk for so long?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.26,0:06:57.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We went all the way to the northern Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.95,0:07:00.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, all the way to the Adelaide Bridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.34,0:07:06.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. But if she doesn't return tomorrow,\Nwe'll have to go look for her in Northern Adelaide again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.24,0:07:09.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Could she have gone\Nto see Dr. Deighton in city of Gawler?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.02,0:07:10.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Impossible! It's too far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.99,0:07:12.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We can never know for sure. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.79,0:07:14.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's true, we can't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.41,0:07:16.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.45,0:07:17.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.57,0:07:21.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Back when it suddenly started to rain, Little...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.75,0:07:45.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter with Little barking so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.52,0:07:47.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.70,0:07:51.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John, let's find shelter from rain somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.66,0:07:52.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.45,0:07:58.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little! Come, boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.87,0:08:05.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Little! What's wrong? Come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.26,0:08:11.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, it was rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.70,0:08:16.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little must've found her trace,\Nbut that heavy rain washed it all away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.44,0:08:21.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. I gotta go look around that bridge once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.97,0:08:23.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going there now?
Comment: 0,0:08:23.44,0:08:24.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.30,0:08:28.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, I can do it tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.65,0:08:31.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, only if Lucy isn't back by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.32,0:08:39.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I was sure you'd find Lucy\Nand bring her home tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.78,0:08:43.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You get it? I'm counting on you\Nto find Lucy for me, by all means.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.50,0:08:54.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! The moon is out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.00,0:08:57.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The weather is awfully whimsical tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.29,0:09:03.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, because the Moon is sitting so high,\Nit'll know for sure, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.77,0:09:06.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please, tell us where Lucy is!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.12,0:10:39.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.80,0:10:42.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is where I went to sleep last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.68,0:10:45.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But before that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.89,0:10:48.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember anything before that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.28,0:11:41.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Little Miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.25,0:11:42.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.14,0:11:46.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You see, there was something\Nthe madam asked of me last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.89,0:11:51.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Should you recollect your name\Nand your parents' names by morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.77,0:11:57.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I guess you still can't remember\Nanything about yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.53,0:12:00.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Why is it so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.98,0:12:04.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How come I know that there are\Nfive fingers on each of my hands,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.52,0:12:09.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,but can't recall my own name,\Nor anything about my father or my mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.56,0:12:14.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little Miss, you shouldn't be crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.17,0:12:15.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's just a medical condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.66,0:12:18.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A medical condition\Nmeans you can recover from it one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.23,0:12:22.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Who am I? Oh, who in the world might I be?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.21,0:12:23.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little Miss...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.63,0:12:26.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little Miss, I'll go call the madam now, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.32,0:12:27.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Better stop crying, Little Miss!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.96,0:13:20.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're cute. What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.96,0:13:46.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Meow! Here! Over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.97,0:13:49.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Squeeze!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.81,0:13:56.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Too slow, too slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.94,0:13:59.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Over here now!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.67,0:14:04.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Ouch, ouch! I give up! I give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.15,0:14:06.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.53,0:14:10.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.72,0:14:13.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Little Miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.58,0:14:16.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The cat's name is Prospero.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.95,0:14:20.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Prospero? Such an unusual name!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.79,0:14:23.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,His namesake is Shakespeare's "The Tempest."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.26,0:14:28.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.48,0:14:31.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't regained your memory yet, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.06,0:14:31.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.71,0:14:34.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.99,0:14:36.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.18,0:14:41.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's nothing. I just couldn't stop the tears,\Nthinking about your plight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.97,0:14:45.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get up now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.94,0:14:48.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can stay as you are now.\NThey'll bring your breakfast soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.10,0:14:50.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.15,0:14:53.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You probably never had\Nbreakfast in bed before, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.05,0:14:56.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Try to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.89,0:14:58.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.92,0:15:09.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to keep you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.07,0:15:14.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, go ahead now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.29,0:15:17.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your service.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.13,0:15:22.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Bon appetit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.84,0:15:27.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're hungry, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.06,0:15:27.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.41,0:15:33.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? You don't like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.41,0:15:37.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's very delicious.\NBut I just can't help this odd feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.24,0:15:38.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.61,0:15:42.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eating in bed like this is very comforting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.01,0:15:44.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like it's the first time I'm doing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.91,0:15:48.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see. But your hand was already halfway to your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.46,0:15:50.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So try to eat it all, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.47,0:15:51.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.52,0:16:02.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's so delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.65,0:16:12.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.59,0:16:21.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I must've inconvenienced you\Na great deal with this affair.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.69,0:16:27.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When I found her lying on the ground, I brought her here completely on the spur of the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.09,0:16:28.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.95,0:16:31.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I actually think you acted like a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.37,0:16:34.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't mind looking after that child?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.08,0:16:35.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'm glad, in fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.65,0:16:36.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.02,0:16:39.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But what will you do about her now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.34,0:16:41.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We need to give her some strong stimulus.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.69,0:16:46.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't do that, her memory might remain\Nforever obscured in the depths of her mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.08,0:16:47.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A strong stimulus...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.61,0:16:51.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. First off, we'll take her to the Adelaide Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.36,0:16:52.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.34,0:16:54.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If we're lucky, she'll regain her memory, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.34,0:16:56.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll take her on a carriage trip around Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.69,0:17:00.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Chances are, we might drive past that girl's home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.14,0:17:03.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If she sees her own home,\Nit might serve as a trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.32,0:17:06.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Someone from her family\Nmight also see and recognize her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.20,0:17:10.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We'll seat her next to the window\Nso that her face can be seen easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.80,0:17:22.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To the Adelaide Bridge, Max.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.37,0:17:23.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.90,0:17:51.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So, Young Miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.55,0:17:53.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Does anything around here look familiar to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.27,0:17:56.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.74,0:18:03.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, her home is just not in this part of town.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.27,0:18:04.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.03,0:18:16.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is where I found you lying on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.06,0:18:16.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.92,0:18:19.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The runaway horse came from that direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.58,0:18:22.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When lying on the ground,\Nhow was she oriented?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.43,0:18:25.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see. Like this, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.10,0:18:29.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That means we can't tell\Nwhich side of the bridge she came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.28,0:18:35.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose. But when I first noticed her,\Nintuitively, I felt that she came from that side.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.23,0:18:37.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, she was heading to Northern Adelaide, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.90,0:18:39.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.00,0:18:42.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, it's possible that her home\Nis in Northern Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.60,0:18:47.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It happened in the evening,\Nso she might have been on her way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.48,0:18:48.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.31,0:18:51.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So? Anything comes to your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.19,0:18:54.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.32,0:18:56.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.79,0:19:10.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is the one most lively street of Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.41,0:19:12.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So? Remember anything now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.84,0:19:14.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.48,0:19:31.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? You're not looking outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.61,0:19:32.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.45,0:19:32.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.87,0:19:34.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm seeing this city for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.87,0:19:38.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It must be that I lived not here,\Nbut in some other city.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.94,0:19:40.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.53,0:19:45.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But here in Southern Australia,\NAdelaide is the only metropolitan city.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.63,0:19:49.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Gawler is the only other similar place nearby\Nthat I can think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.39,0:19:50.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Gawler?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.08,0:19:52.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.39,0:20:07.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty sure it was around here\Nwhere Little bizarrely started barking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.49,0:20:10.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see anything wrong at all with this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.91,0:20:14.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even if there was something,\Nyesterday's rain washed it all away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.86,0:20:16.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.72,0:20:17.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.94,0:20:19.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We should go check in Gawler.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.96,0:20:21.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Gawler, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.16,0:20:24.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. If we take a cart,\Nit's not that awfully far away, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.58,0:20:25.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.23,0:20:30.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've been having this feeling\Nthat Lucy went to Dr. Deighton for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.10,0:20:33.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then we gotta think about someone\Nwho'd let us take a carriage to there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.45,0:20:35.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hire one, father.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.53,0:20:35.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.80,0:21:15.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mom! Mom! It's serious, mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.96,0:21:17.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.46,0:21:19.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy was there!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.42,0:21:20.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What? Did she come home?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.79,0:21:22.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, she rode a carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.50,0:21:23.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A carriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.14,0:21:26.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. She watched at me\Nfrom the window of a luxurious carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.54,0:21:29.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't be saying lies, Tob.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.08,0:21:33.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's true! It's the truest true! It totally was Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.10,0:21:36.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And then? Did Lucy say something to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.91,0:21:38.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.32,0:21:42.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When she saw me, she didn't even smile.\NIt was as though she's seeing me for the first time!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.82,0:21:46.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And then, which way did that carriage go?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.52,0:21:48.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry! Hurry after me! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.09,0:21:51.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It really was her, decisively!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.77,0:21:56.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Which way, Tob?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.88,0:21:58.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That way!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.30,0:22:04.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like it left...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.90,0:22:09.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.14,0:22:12.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good question.\NFor now, let's just turn back to the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.91,0:22:15.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There's some place I'd like to visit first.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.89,0:22:18.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.30,0:22:20.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.84,0:22:42.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.30,0:22:49.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, how adorable!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.02,0:22:51.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It fits her greatly. Don't you think so, dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.17,0:22:52.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.40,0:22:58.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's it inconvenient that we don't know your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.85,0:23:04.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Until you recall your own name,\NI'll be calling you Emily, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.89,0:23:06.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Understand, Emily?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.77,0:23:09.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, Emily was the name of...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.39,0:23:13.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed. That Emily was brought back to life.
Comment: 0,0:23:13.51,0:23:14.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.44,0:23:15.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.41,0:23:19.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go. I'll give you a tour through the garden, Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.46,0:23:26.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is on your mind, Sylvia?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.55,0:23:31.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come, this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.39,0:24:07.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The sir and madam treat me kindly\Nas if I was their own daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.59,0:24:09.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But who am I, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.75,0:24:13.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Next on Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow:\N"A Child Called Emily".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.91,0:24:15.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
